3.00	Wordiness	Verbosity	Verbosity (also called wordiness, prolixity and garrulousness) in language refers to speech or writing which is deemed to use an excess of words. Adjectival forms are verbose, wordy, prolix and garrulous.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/1/13/Julius_Caesar_Coustou_Louvre.png/130px-Julius_Caesar_Coustou_Louvre.png
